Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses an information theoretic approach to analyze the impact of C-RAN architecture in the presence of full-duplex base stations. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of cellular systems and investigates the impact of C-RAN architecture on downlink-to-uplink interference among base stations. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the design and operation of cellular systems and investigates the impact of C-RAN architecture on interference cancellation. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design and operation of cellular systems and investigates the impact of C-RAN architecture on interference cancellation and mobile station scheduling. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the design and operation of cellular systems and investigates the impact of C-RAN architecture on interference cancellation and mobile station scheduling, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
